{
  "stem": "10818.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she was from a town called Nierstein nearby, and, and also been in the wine business for a long time.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But anyway, my father tried, literally everything, from the time we came here, to get her out of, out of Germany.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He tried to get her transferred to our quota number.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because my mother was still there, and it was going through.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I would like to tell you about my mother's experiences, too.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] He wrote to the President of the United States, to, to try and get this quota number.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Of course, I mean, it was all for nothing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was-- in a way, he knew it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He wasn't that naive that he didn't, but he just could not leave any stone unturned trying to get her to come to this country, trying to save her.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He tried to get her to Cuba, which is what Frank's parents did.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And that no longer worked.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And of course once, once we were-- in-- after Pearl Harbor, once we were in the war, there was no way of doing it anymore.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I can't say that for sure.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were just going around and-- they were not our neighbors.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were a face-- basically to me, at least-- a faceless mob.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, this is, you know, you're talking about a town the size of Trenton.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You don't, you don't know everybody who's going around.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I do not think they were the middle class people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I mean, I don't-- I still don't think that ordinary, middle class people will go around in mobs, in looting.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They may have been children of middle class people who didn't know any better, who came with their classmates or what have you.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But they were, you know, rabble, mob.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
